{"word":"βαρέω","slug":"βαρέω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>βαρέω</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:βαρύς'><el>βαρύς</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to weigh down, depress</i>, <b><a href='S:Lucian'>Luc.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:intransitive'>intr.</a> in epic <a href='S:perfect tense'>perf.</a> <a href='S:participle'>part.</a> <el>βεβαρηώς</el>, <i>weighed down, heavy</i>, <el>οἴνωι βεβαρηότες</el> <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b>: later in <a href='S:participle'>part.</a> <a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>pass.</a></a> <el>βεβαρημένος</el>, <b><a href='S:Theocritus'>Theocr.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Anthology'>Anth.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div>"}]}